==English==

===Etymology===
From ''[[a-]]'' "on" + Old English ''baft'', ''baften'', ''biaften'', Anglo Saxon ''beæftan''; ''be'' "by" + ''æftan'' "behind". See [[after]], [[aft]], [[by]]

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːft|-ɑːft]]

===Preposition===
'''abaft'''

# {{nautical}} [[behind|Behind]]; toward the [[stern]] [[relative]] to some other [[object]] or [[position]]; as, ''abaft'' the [[wheelhouse]].

====Derived terms====
*[[abaft the beam]]

